artimento, pp. 131\u201348. London: Routledge |year=2017 |isbn=978-1-472-47327-1}}\n* {{citation |last=van Tour |title=Improvised and Written Canons in Eighteenth-Century Neapolitan Conservatories |publisher=Journal of the Alamire Foundation 10, pp. 133\u201346. Turnhout: Brepols Publishers |year=2018 |issn=2032-5371}}\n* {{citation |last=Paraschivescu |title=Die Partimenti Giovanni Paisiellos Wege zu einem praxisbezogenen Verst\u00e4ndnis |publisher=Schwabe Verlag, Basel |year=2018 |isbn=978-3-7965-3724-0}}\n* {{citation |last=van Tour |title=Integrating Aural and Keyboard Skills in Today's Classroom: Modern Perspectives on Eighteenth-Century Partimento Practices | publisher=Keyboard Skills in Musical Education: Historical and Contemporary Perspectives, Freiburg: Freiburg Hochschule. |year=2020}}\n* {{citation |last=IJzerman |title=Harmony, Counterpoint, Partimento: A New Method Inspired by Old Masters | publisher=Oxford University Press |year=2019|isbn=9780190695019}}\n* {{citation |last=van Tour |title=Taking a walk at the Molo\u2019: Partimento and the Improvised Fugue | publisher=Musical Improvisation in the Baroque Era, Turnhout, Brepols, Speculum Musicae, 33, pp. 371\u201382 |year=2019|isbn=978-2-503-58369-3}}\n* {{citation |last=Gjerdingen |title=Child Composers in the Old Conservatories: How Orphans Became Elite Musicians | publisher=Oxford University Press |year=2020|isbn=9780190653590}}\n{{refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://partimenti.org/partimenti/index.html Monuments of Partimenti]\n* [http://www2.musik.uu.se/UUPart/UUPart.php The Uppsala Partimento Database, UUPart. Compiled and edited by Peter van Tour. Launched 2015, Uppsala.] \n* [https://partimentiscarlatti.blogspot.com/ The partimenti of Alessandro Scarlatti (D-Hs M/A 251)] \n\n[[Category:Classical music]]\n[[Category:Musical analysis]]\n[[Category:Musical improvisation]]\n[[Category:Classical period (music)]]\n[[Category:Baroque music]]\n[[Category:18th century in music]]\n[[Category:17th century in music]]\n[[Category:19th century in music]]\n[[Category:18th-century Italian musicians]]\n[[Category:Accompaniment]]\n[[Category:Neapolitan school composers]]\n[[Category:Music theory]]\n[[Category:Musicology]]\n[[Category:Music history]]\n", "name_user": "Ronster2019", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Partimento"}
{"title_page": "Naa... Nuvve", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2018}}\n{{infobox film\n| name           = Naa... Nuvve\n| image          = Naa... Nuvve poster.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| studio         =<br />Cool Breeze Cinemas\n| director       = Jayendra Panchapakesan\n| writer         = [[Subha (writers)|Subha]]<br />Jayendra Panchapakesan<br /> [[Suryaa (screenwriter)|Suryaa]]\n| starring       = [[Nandamuri Kalyan Ram]]<br />[[Tamannaah]]<br />[[Vennela Kishore]]\n| music          = [[Sharreth]]\n| cinematography = [[P. C. Sreeram]]\n| producer       = Kiran Muppavarpu<br />Vijaykumar Vattikuti\n| country        = [[India]]\n| language       = Telugu\n| released       = {{Film date|df=y|2018|06|14}}\n| runtime        = 125 minutes\n}}\n'''''Naa... Nuvve''''' ({{trans|You're mine}}) is a [[Telugu language]] [[romantic drama]] film written and directed by Jayendra Panchapakesan and produced by Kiran Muppavarapu and Vijay Kumar Vattikuti under Cool Breeze Cinemas banner while Mahesh S Koneru is presenting the film on East Coast Productions banner.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehansindia.com/posts/index/Tollywood/2018-04-16/Naa-Nuvve-Song-Promo-on-April-18th/374456 |title=\"Naa Nuvve\" Song Promo on April 18th |date=16 April 2018 |work=[[The Hans India]] |access-date=16 April 2018}}</ref> It features [[Nandamuri Kalyan Ram]] and [[Tamannaah]] in the lead roles.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/tamannaah-nandamuri-kalyan-ram-naa-nuvve-first-glimpse/1/1125868.html |title=Tamannaah and Nandamuri Kalyan Rams Naa Nuvve first glimpse promises a breezy love story |date=8 January 2018 |work=[[India Today]] |access-date=9 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/tollywood/270817/tamannaah-bhatia-cast-opposite-kalyan-ram.html | title=Not Aishwarya Lekshmi, Tamannaah Bhatia to star in Kalyan Ram's next | work=Deccan Chronicle | date=27 August 2017 | accessdate=28 August 2017 | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170828123026/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/tollywood/270817/tamannaah-bhatia-cast-opposite-kalyan-ram.html | archivedate=28 August 2017 }}</ref> [[P. C. Sreeram]] was the cinematographer and [[Sharreth]] composed the film's music. The film released on June 14, 2018, worldwide.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/news/its-a-wrap-up-for-nandamuri-kalyanrams-naa-nuvve/articleshow/63682025.cms |title=It\u2019s a wrap up for Nandamuri Kalyanram's \u2018Naa Nuvve\u2019 |date=9 April 2018 |work=[[The Times of India]]|access-date=9 April 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Plot ==\nTrue love is fulfilling. Meera is a happy go lucky radio jockey who ends up falling in love with a very confident Varun who is nothing like Meera in life. How far will Varun and Meera go to get their love that truly completes them.\n\n== Cast ==\n* [[Nandamuri Kalyan Ram]] as Varun\n* [[Tamannaah]] as Meera\n* [[Tanikella Bharani]] as Meera's father\n* [[Posani Krishna Murali]]\n* [[Vennela Kishore]]\n* [[Surekha Vani]]\n* [[Chevella Ravi]]\n* Kalyani\n* [[Praveen (actor)|Praveen]] as Ravi\n* [[Shekar Basha]] as FM Radio Jockey\n\n==Soundtrack==\nThe Music Was Composed By [[Sharreth]] and Released by [[Sony Music India]].\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Naa... Nuvve\n| type       = [[Soundtrack]]\n| artist     = [[Sharreth]]\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = May 7, 2018\n| recorded   = 2018\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Soundtrack]]\n| length     = 20:36\n| label      = [[Sony Music India]]\n| producer   = [[Sharreth]]\n| prev_title = [[Hadiyya]]\n| prev_year  = 2017\n| next_title = [[Parole (film)|Parole]]\n| next_year  = 2018\n}}\n\n{{Tracklist\n| collapsed       =\n| headline        = Track list\n| extra_column    = Artist(s)\n| total_length    = 20:36\n| title1          = Hey Hey ILU (Male Version)\n| lyrics1         = [[Anantha Sriram]]\n| extra1          = [[Tippu (singer)|Tippu]]\n| length1         = 2:27\n| title2          = Nijama Manasa\n| lyrics2         = [[Anantha Sriram]]\n| extra2          = [[Yazin Nizar]], [[M. M. Manasi]]\n| length2         = 3:27\n| title3          = Right Right Right\n| lyrics3         = [[Ramajogayya Sastry]]\n| extra3          = [[Tippu (singer)|Tippu]]\n| length3         = 2:34\n| title4          = Chiniki Chiniki\n| lyrics4         = [[Anantha Sriram]]\n| extra4          = Saptaparna Chakraborty, [[Karthik (singer)|karthik]]\n| length4         = 3:06\n| title5          = Premika\n| lyrics5         = [[Anantha Sriram]]\n| extra5          = [[Sharreth]]\n| length5         = 2:53\n| title6           = Naa Nuvve\n| lyrics6         = [[Ramajogayya Sastry]]\n| extra6          = [[Priya Mali]]\n| length6          =3:42\n| title7           = Hey Hey ILU (Female Version)\n| lyrics7         = [[Anantha Sriram]]\n| extra7          = [[Rita (Indian singer)|Rita]]\n| length7          =2:27\n}}\n\n== Release ==\nThe film was released worldwide on 14 June 2018. The film's Hindi dubbed version titled ''Diljala Aashiq'' will soon be released on [[YouTube]] by Goldmines Telefilms in 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UfcqGpGYF9Y|title=Diljala Aashiq (Naa Nuvve) 2019 Hindi Dubbed Trailer - Nandamuri Kalyan Ram, Tamannaah Bhatia}}</ref>\n\n===Critical reception===\n''[[The Times of India]]'' rated the film 2/5 and called it \"A dull and lifeless take on love and destiny!\".<ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movie-reviews/naa-nuvve/movie-review/64584707.cms</ref>\n123 Telugu rated the film 2.75/5 and called it \"a routine romantic drama which gets distracted by some wayward execution.\"<ref>https://www.123telugu.com/reviews/kalyan-ram-naa-nuvve-movie-review.html</ref>\nGreatandhra rated the film 2/5 and says \"Looks like it was written on one-line idea, and director and his writers have woven silly scenes to this single point idea.\"<ref>https://www.greatandhra.com/movies/reviews/naa-nuvve-review-bad-destiny-90097.html</ref>\n[https://www.advancetips.site/2020/04/diljala-aashiq-naa-nuvve-2020-new-released-hindi-dubbed-full-movie-2020.html Watch Now in hindi dubbed language]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|tt7838158}}\n\n[[Category:2018 films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2010s Telugu-language films]]\n[[Category:2010s romantic comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:Indian romantic comedy-drama films]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2018}}\n{{infobox film\n| name           = Naa... Nuvve\n| image          = Naa... Nuvve poster.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| studio         =<br />Cool Breeze Cinemas\n| director       = Jayendra Panchapakesan\n| writer         = [[Subha (writers)|Subha]]<br />Jayendra Panchapakesan<br /> [[Suryaa (screenwriter)|Suryaa]]\n| starring       = [[Nandamuri Kalyan Ram]]<br />[[Tamannaah]]<br />[[Vennela Kishore]]\n| music          = [[Sharreth]]\n| cinematography = [[P. C. Sreeram]]\n| producer       = Kiran Muppavarpu<br />Vijaykumar Vattikuti\n| country        = [[India]]\n| language       = Telugu\n| released       = {{Film date|df=y|2018|06|14}}\n| runtime        = 125 minutes\n}}\n'''''Naa... Nuvve''''' ({{trans|You're mine}}) is a [[Telugu language]] [[romantic drama]] film written and directed by Jayendra Panchapakesan and produced by Kiran Muppavarapu and Vijay Kumar Vattikuti under Cool Breeze Cinemas banner while Mahesh S Koneru is presenting the film on East Coast Productions banner.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehansindia.com/posts/index/Tollywood/2018-04-16/Naa-Nuvve-Song-Promo-on-April-18th/374456 |title=\"Naa Nuvve\" Song Promo on April 18th |date=16 April 2018 |work=[[The Hans India]] |access-date=16 April 2018}}</ref> It features [[Nandamuri Kalyan Ram]] and [[Tamannaah]] in the lead roles.<ref>{{Cite